<subSubSection id="68FAE8DEFFA6FFAF2CA4D862FD4BFB95" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="835" pageId="10" pageNumber="834" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="205FBB55FFA6FFAE2CA4D862FB4DFC3B" blockId="10.[685,1173,368,1730]" pageId="10" pageNumber="834">
<emphasis id="12946747FFA6FFAE2CA4D862FCFFFD95" bold="true" box="[709,807,611,632]" pageId="10" pageNumber="834">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species has a confused history with a surprising ending. Originally described from 
<collectingCountry id="58F7FBC5FFA6FFAE2CCCD899FCF8FD40" box="[685,800,664,685]" name="Guadeloupe" pageId="10" pageNumber="834">Guadeloupe</collectingCountry>
in 
<taxonomicName id="E7E0C0D6FFA6FFAE2D5AD899FB48FD40" authority="Laporte and Brulle, 1831" authorityName="Laporte and Brulle" authorityYear="1831" box="[827,1168,664,686]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Platydema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="834" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="12946747FFA6FFAE2D5AD899FC78FD43" box="[827,928,664,686]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="834">Platydema</emphasis>
Laporte and Brullé, 1831
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<typeStatus id="FF5B05F7FFA6FFAE2CB7D8B2FD27FD25" box="[726,767,691,712]" pageId="10" pageNumber="834">type</typeStatus>
was said to be in the Louis Alexandre Auguste Chevrolat (1799–1884) collection, the tenebrionid portion of which is housed today in the collection of Léon Marc Herminie Fairmaire (1820–1906) in the Muséum national d’ Histoire naturelle, Paris (Horn and Kahle 1935). This specimen has not been reported on since the original description, in spite of the fact that the tenebrionids of 
<collectingCountry id="58F7FBC5FFA6FFAE2CB2D98AFC9EFC4D" box="[723,838,907,928]" name="Guadeloupe" pageId="10" pageNumber="834">Guadeloupe</collectingCountry>
have been treated four times (Fleutiaux and Sallé 1889; Marcuzzi and d’ Aguilar 1971; 
<bibRefCitation id="4471C6A4FFA6FFAE2C89D9C0FC53FC3B" author="Chalumeau, F." box="[744,907,961,982]" pageId="10" pageNumber="834" pagination="187 - 195" refId="ref9836" refString="Chalumeau, F. 1982. Tenebrionidae des Antilles francaises: Description d' une nouvelle espece, designation de lectotypes et observations diverse (Col). Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France 87: 187 - 195." type="journal article" year="1982">Chalumeau 1982</bibRefCitation>
; Soldati and Touroult 2014).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="205FBB55FFA6FFAE2CA4D9DDFC62FA88" blockId="10.[685,1173,368,1730]" pageId="10" pageNumber="834">
Fleutiaux and Sallé (1889) treated it as a 
<taxonomicName id="E7E0C0D6FFA6FFAE2A3BD9DAFD39FBE1" authorityName="Laporte and Brulle" authorityYear="1831" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Platydema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="834" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="12946747FFA6FFAE2A3BD9DAFD39FBE1" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="834">Platydema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but only cited its description, adding nothing to indicate they knew the species. The species appeared without explanation in 
<taxonomicName id="E7E0C0D6FFA6FFAE2A68DE2AFBA9FBAC" authorityName="Spiessberger &amp; Ivie" authorityYear="2018" box="[1033,1137,1067,1089]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Cyrtosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="834" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="12946747FFA6FFAE2A68DE2AFBA9FBAC" box="[1033,1137,1067,1089]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="834">Cyrtosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Gebien’ s (1911) catalog. If it was moved earlier than that, we have been unable to find the reference. Zoological Record has no mention of this action, and Soldati and Touroult (2014) were also unable to find the origin of this transfer. After Gebien’ s (1911) catalog, it was listed under 
<taxonomicName id="E7E0C0D6FFA6FFAE2DCFDECBFBCEFB0D" authorityName="Spiessberger &amp; Ivie" authorityYear="2018" box="[942,1046,1226,1248]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Cyrtosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="834" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="12946747FFA6FFAE2DCFDECBFBCEFB0D" box="[942,1046,1226,1248]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="834">Cyrtosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with varying levels of doubt several times (
<emphasis id="12946747FFA6FFAE2D98DEE7FBCEFB16" box="[1017,1046,1254,1275]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="834">e.g</emphasis>
., Leng and Mutchler 1914). It even appeared a few times as two species, being included under both genera (
<emphasis id="12946747FFA6FFAE2A0ADF1AFB50FADD" box="[1131,1160,1307,1328]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="834">e.g</emphasis>
., Marcuzzi and d’ Aguilar 1971; 
<bibRefCitation id="4471C6A4FFA6FFAE2D87DF34FB48FAA7" author="Peck, S. B." box="[998,1168,1332,1354]" pageId="10" pageNumber="834" pagination="1 - 156" refId="ref11931" refString="Peck, S. B., M. C. Thomas, and R. H. Turnbow. 2014. The diversity and distributions of the beetles (Insecta: Coleoptera) of the Guadeloupe archipelago (Grand Terre, Basse Terre, La Desirade, Marie- Galante, Les Saintes, and Petite-Terre), Lesser Antilles. Insecta Mundi 352: 1 - 156." type="journal article" year="2014">
Peck 
<emphasis id="12946747FFA6FFAE2A7EDF34FB8BFAA7" box="[1055,1107,1332,1354]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="834">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
; Soldati and Touroult 2014).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="205FBB55FFA6FFAE2CA4DF6BFBC9F99F" blockId="10.[685,1173,368,1730]" pageId="10" pageNumber="834">
<bibRefCitation id="4471C6A4FFA6FFAE2CA4DF6BFCB6FA92" author="Marcuzzi, G." box="[709,878,1386,1407]" pageId="10" pageNumber="834" pagination="235 - 252" refId="ref11442" refString="Marcuzzi, G. 1991. New species of Cyrtosoma Perty (Coleoptera: Tenebrionidae) from the Neotropical region. Elytron 5: 235 - 252." type="journal article" year="1991">Marcuzzi (1991)</bibRefCitation>
included it in his key to 
<taxonomicName id="E7E0C0D6FFA6FFAE2CCCDF85FCCDFA77" authorityName="Spiessberger &amp; Ivie" authorityYear="2018" box="[685,789,1412,1434]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Cyrtosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="834" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="12946747FFA6FFAE2CCCDF85FCCDFA77" box="[685,789,1412,1434]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="834">Cyrtosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and he acknowledged the BMNH as the source of “all the present material.” A search of the collection there did not unearth any specimen with that name (Maxwell Barclay, 
<emphasis id="12946747FFA6FFAE2DA6DFD7FC22FA06" box="[967,1018,1493,1515]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="834">in litt</emphasis>
.), and, from the characters in the key, it would appear its inclusion is based on the original description, not a specimen. As such, apparently no specimen attributed to 
<taxonomicName id="E7E0C0D6FFA6FFAE2AE3DC26FD38F9BA" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Cyrtosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="834" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picea">
<emphasis id="12946747FFA6FFAE2AE3DC26FD38F9BA" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="834">P. picea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been seen by anyone publishing on this species since its original description.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="205FBB55FFA6FFAF2CA4DC76FD55FE9B" blockId="10.[685,1173,368,1730]" lastBlockId="11.[173,660,193,1198]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="835" pageId="10" pageNumber="834">
Judging from the description, Laporte and Brullé’ s species is simply not a 
<collectingCountry id="58F7FBC5FFA6FFAE2DCBDC93FBC2F94A" box="[938,1050,1682,1703]" name="Guadeloupe" pageId="10" pageNumber="834">Guadeloupe</collectingCountry>
<taxonomicName id="E7E0C0D6FFA6FFAE2A46DC90FB55F94A" authorityName="Spiessberger &amp; Ivie" authorityYear="2018" box="[1063,1165,1681,1703]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Cyrtosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="834" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="12946747FFA6FFAE2A46DC90FB55F94A" box="[1063,1165,1681,1703]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="834">Cyrtosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Antoine Mantilleri located the 
<typeStatus id="FF5B05F7FFA6FFAE2DA8DCACFC29F92F" box="[969,1009,1709,1730]" pageId="10" pageNumber="834">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="E7E0C0D6FFA6FFAE2A71DCACFB82F92F" box="[1040,1114,1709,1730]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Cyrtosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="834" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picea">
<emphasis id="12946747FFA6FFAE2A71DCACFBC4F92F" box="[1040,1052,1709,1730]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="834">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="12946747FFA6FFAE2A46DCACFB82F92F" box="[1063,1114,1709,1730]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="834">picea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at our request, and provided photographs (
<figureCitation id="B8DBA7D0FFA7FFAF2F9CDAC3FDB6FF3A" box="[509,622,193,215]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="6.[175,214,875,894]" captionTargetBox="[156,1167,196,857]" captionTargetId="figure-462@6.[154,1169,194,859]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs. 13–14. Hesiodus piceus, syntype. 13) Habitus; 14) Labels. ©MNHN/A. Mantilleri." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5386574" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5386574/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="835">Figs. 13–14</figureCitation>
), in fact revealing that it is conspecific with 
<taxonomicName id="E7E0C0D6FFA7FFAF2C5DDADAFE2BFEE1" authority="Fleutiaux and Salle, 1889" authorityName="Fleutiaux and Salle" authorityYear="1889" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Hesiodus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="835" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caraibus">
<emphasis id="12946747FFA7FFAF2C5DDADAFF26FEE1" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="835">Hesiodus caraibus</emphasis>
Fleutiaux and Sallé, 1889
</taxonomicName>
. It is unfortunate, but unavoidable, that the older and poorly known name must replace the well-established one, but its recent use as a valid name requires us to retain the junior synonym under Art. 23.9.1.1. (ICZN 1999).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="205FBB55FFA7FFAF2EA4DB7DFD4CFD77" blockId="11.[173,660,193,1198]" pageId="11" pageNumber="835">
The first label with the specimen (
<figureCitation id="B8DBA7D0FFA7FFAF2C46DB7DFDA8FE7C" box="[551,624,380,401]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="6.[175,214,875,894]" captionTargetBox="[156,1167,196,857]" captionTargetId="figure-462@6.[154,1169,194,859]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs. 13–14. Hesiodus piceus, syntype. 13) Habitus; 14) Labels. ©MNHN/A. Mantilleri." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5386574" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5386574/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="835">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
) is in the hand of Ferdinand Joseph L’ Herminier (1802–1866). The third label appears to be in the hand of Chevrolat. Thus, the specimen matches the information in Laporte and Brullé’ s (1831) description. The use of the name 
<taxonomicName id="E7E0C0D6FFA7FFAF2C66D801FDB7FDFB" authorityName="Spiessberger &amp; Ivie" authorityYear="2018" box="[519,623,512,534]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Cyrtosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="835" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="12946747FFA7FFAF2C66D801FDB7FDFB" box="[519,623,512,534]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="835">Cyrtosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Chevrolat apparently predates the description as a manuscript name, and this third label could be the source of Gebien’ s placement, even though Chevrolat’ s concept associated with that manuscript name differed from what was eventually published.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="205FBB55FFA7FFAF2EA4D8A1FD4BFB95" blockId="11.[173,660,193,1198]" pageId="11" pageNumber="835">
The question of the specimen’ s status as the 
<typeStatus id="FF5B05F7FFA7FFAF2ECCD8BBFED8FD22" box="[173,256,698,719]" pageId="11" pageNumber="835">holotype</typeStatus>
or a 
<typeStatus id="FF5B05F7FFA7FFAF2F2DD8BBFE4EFD22" box="[332,406,698,719]" pageId="11" pageNumber="835">syntype</typeStatus>
is unclear. Clearly, the 
<typeStatus id="FF5B05F7FFA7FFAF2ECCD8D4FF2FFD07" box="[173,247,725,746]" pageId="11" pageNumber="835">syntype</typeStatus>
label was added long after the original description. ICZN (1999) Recommendation 73F suggests that an assumption of 
<typeStatus id="FF5B05F7FFA7FFAF2F83D90BFDEDFCF2" box="[482,565,778,799]" pageId="11" pageNumber="835">holotype</typeStatus>
status be avoided in the absence of a clear statement of a singleton in a description before 2000. Other than the fact there is only a single measurement in the description of 
<taxonomicName id="E7E0C0D6FFA7FFAF2F22D975FE4CFC64" box="[323,404,884,905]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Cyrtosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="835" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picea">
<emphasis id="12946747FFA7FFAF2F22D975FE4CFC64" box="[323,404,884,905]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="835">P. picea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, there is nothing to definitively say there was only a single type specimen. We feel the curators in Paris have acted correctly in considering this specimen a 
<typeStatus id="FF5B05F7FFA7FFAF2FDED9C5FDD4FC34" box="[447,524,964,985]" pageId="11" pageNumber="835">syntype</typeStatus>
. Since we are not revising 
<taxonomicName id="E7E0C0D6FFA7FFAF2F4BD9DFFE5AFC19" authorityName="Champion" authorityYear="1885" box="[298,386,990,1012]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Hesiodus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="835" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="12946747FFA7FFAF2F4BD9DFFE5AFC19" box="[298,386,990,1012]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="835">Hesiodus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we will not designate this specimen as a 
<typeStatus id="FF5B05F7FFA7FFAF2F21D9F8FE41FBE3" box="[320,409,1017,1038]" pageId="11" pageNumber="835">lectotype</typeStatus>
, leaving that for a future reviser. In a similar case, Laporte and Brullé (1831) also named 
<taxonomicName id="E7E0C0D6FFA7FFAF2F4DDE2FFEF5FBB3" authority="(Laporte and Brulle, 1831)" baseAuthorityName="Laporte and Brulle" baseAuthorityYear="1831" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Nesocyrtosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="835" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="virens">
<emphasis id="12946747FFA7FFAF2F4DDE2FFDDDFBAE" box="[300,517,1070,1091]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="835">Nesocyrtosoma virens</emphasis>
(Laporte and Brullé, 1831)
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName id="E7E0C0D6FFA7FFAF2F2FDE49FD57FBB3" authority="(Hopp and Ivie 2009)" baseAuthorityName="Hopp and Ivie" baseAuthorityYear="2009" box="[334,655,1096,1118]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Platydema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="835" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="12946747FFA7FFAF2F2FDE49FE6BFBB3" box="[334,435,1096,1118]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="835">Platydema</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="4471C6A4FFA7FFAF2FA3DE48FD50FBB3" author="Hopp, K. J." box="[450,648,1097,1118]" pageId="11" pageNumber="835" pagination="1 - 138" refId="ref10437" refString="Hopp, K. J., and M. A. Ivie. 2009. Revision of the West Indian genus Nesocyrtosoma Marcuzzi (Coleoptera: Tenebrionidae). The Coleopterists Society Monograph Number 8: 1 - 138." type="book chapter" year="2009">Hopp and Ivie 2009</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="E7E0C0D6FFA7FFAF2EB7DE65FEB0FB94" authorityName="Marcuzzi" authorityYear="1976" box="[214,360,1124,1145]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Nesocyrtosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="835" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="12946747FFA7FFAF2EB7DE65FEB0FB94" box="[214,360,1124,1145]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="835">Nesocyrtosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a close relative of 
<taxonomicName id="E7E0C0D6FFA7FFAF2C54DE62FD55FB94" authorityName="Champion" authorityYear="1885" box="[565,653,1123,1145]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Hesiodus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="835" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="12946747FFA7FFAF2C54DE62FD55FB94" box="[565,653,1123,1145]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="835">Hesiodus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
